1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:09,886
I saved the best insight for right here,  Consumers send heartbeats to the Group Coordinator on a background thread every heartbeat.interval.ms (default 3 s).

2
00:00:09,836 --> 00:00:18,759
If the coordinator doesn't hear from a consumer within session.timeout.ms (default 45 s), it declares the consumer dead and triggers a rebalance.

3
00:00:18,759 --> 00:00:27,211
Separately, if the consumer doesn't call poll() within max.poll.interval.ms (default 5 min), it's also considered failed.

4
00:00:27,211 --> 00:00:32,480
This catches consumers that are alive (sending heartbeats) , but stuck in slow processing.

5
00:00:32,480 --> 00:00:37,346
Real talk: I've seen senior engineers at Uber get this wrong in interviews.

6
00:00:37,346 --> 00:00:39,096
Don't be that person.

7
00:00:39,096 --> 00:00:43,634
Most developers think more Interview Reality Check means better performance.

8
00:00:43,634 --> 00:00:46,153
It can , actually make things worse.

9
00:00:46,153 --> 00:00:47,903
Stay tuned to see why.

